00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:37,660
[The video ends with a lukewarm reaction]

264
00:12:37,660 --> 00:12:41,480
Directors Park So Rang and
Go Hyeon Guk's video ended.

265
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,620
They got 22 votes.

266
00:12:43,620 --> 00:12:48,250
I don't think it was that many votes,

267
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:51,710
but considering the directors' reputation,

268
00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:54,650
it must have been damaging.

269
00:12:54,650 --> 00:12:57,900
It's not a satisfying result.

270
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:01,470
But I should accept it since this is
how survival shows are.

271
00:13:01,470 --> 00:13:05,140
I was studying when the
stop count started going up.

272
00:13:05,140 --> 00:13:09,580
The scene after the one-minute mark
is actually one scene.

273
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:12,910
The scene where he talks to the doctor.

274
00:13:12,910 --> 00:13:17,260
There was a lot of medical jargon
because of the genre.

275
00:13:17,260 --> 00:13:20,110
I was worried that it might've been a bit long,

276
00:13:20,110 --> 00:13:23,440
but as expected, the number went up.

277
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,880
I was impressed at how sharp people were.

278
00:13:25,880 --> 00:13:29,870
You need to introduce something else
when a part starts getting boring.

279
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:31,570
For me...

280
00:13:31,570 --> 00:13:34,100
- I keep coming clean.
- You pressed it, didn't you?

281
00:13:34,100 --> 00:13:36,960
I pressed it this time. I'm sorry.

282
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:39,600
- You're confessing voluntarily.
- At what point?

283
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:42,000
The part where he mentioned.

284
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,980
It started getting boring at that point.

285
00:13:44,980 --> 00:13:47,520
That kind of acting is hard to pull off.

286
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:50,880
It is. I can relate.

287
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:55,140
That part was a bit difficult to get into.

288
00:13:55,140 --> 00:14:00,220
I once again realized music plays a big part.

289
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:02,870
It could've been just the background music,

290
00:14:02,870 --> 00:14:07,190
but the music changed the mood in every scene.

291
00:14:07,190 --> 00:14:13,520
I sensed that the music in it was very good.

292
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,470
Let me nitpick a little bit.

293
00:14:15,470 --> 00:14:18,750
When he bumps shoulders
with the nurse in the beginning

294
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:24,130
and when his future self kicked
him in the stomach,

295
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:27,550
it felt awkward because I could tell it was fake.

296
00:14:27,550 --> 00:14:33,130
I wish you had made it
a little bit more realistic.

297
00:14:33,130 --> 00:14:36,200
Overall, I thought...

298
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:40,040
it was like well-made seaweed soup
without sesame oil.

299
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,910
It was a bit disappointing.

300
00:14:41,910 --> 00:14:45,710
Jang Keun Suk called it a seaweed
soup without sesame oil.

301
00:14:45,710 --> 00:14:48,760
I'll only look at sesame oil from now on.

302
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:51,620
I'll show you a ton of sesame oil.

303
00:14:51,620 --> 00:14:54,330
Wait, hold on.

304
00:14:54,330 --> 00:14:58,850
I heard Director Lee Beom Gyu
made a cameo appearance.

305
00:14:58,850 --> 00:15:01,890
- Where was he?
- What scene was it?

306
00:15:01,890 --> 00:15:05,390
The loan shark who kicks the future Jin Hyeon.

307
00:15:05,390 --> 00:15:07,410
- He's the culprit.
- That's where it went wrong.

308
00:15:07,410 --> 00:15:09,940
The casting choice was off.

309
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:11,320
He worked with us, too.

310
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:14,660
- He worked with them, too.
- Gosh, seriously.

311
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:16,530
What? Why didn't he help us?

312
00:15:16,530 --> 00:15:19,000
- He wanted to be in another episode.
- Thank you.

313
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:23,090
I could tell he had never hit anyone before.

314
00:15:23,090 --> 00:15:26,620
He is actually a good person.

315
00:15:26,620 --> 00:15:29,260
He couldn't hit hard because
he didn't want to hurt him.

316
00:15:29,260 --> 00:15:31,730
- I can understand.
- He's tender-hearted.

317
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:34,350
You have to say,
"Hit hard and finish in one cut."

318
00:15:34,350 --> 00:15:38,570
Kicking like that probably doesn't hurt.

319
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:42,210
Kicking scenes felt too fake.

320
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:44,440
That's when I pressed it right away.

321
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:48,260
Team "Medical Rebirth" got 22 stops.

322
00:15:48,260 --> 00:15:52,250
What could be their average viewing time?

323
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:55,190
I'll reveal the result now.

324
00:15:55,190 --> 00:15:57,140
This could be unpredictable.

325
00:15:57,140 --> 00:16:01,480
It's all about when those
22 people pressed the button.

326
00:16:02,270 --> 00:16:05,000
- A lot of them pressed later.
- That's true.

327
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:09,950
Reveal the average viewing time
for "Medical Rebirth."

328
00:16:12,380 --> 00:16:17,380
[Did their fantastic teamwork help or hurt them?]

329
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,700
[And the result is?]

330
00:16:20,950 --> 00:16:22,510
What?

331
00:16:24,620 --> 00:16:26,170
["Team Rebirth" gets 103.34 seconds]

332
00:16:26,170 --> 00:16:27,870
It's over 100 seconds.

333
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:30,430
They went past 100 seconds.

334
00:16:30,430 --> 00:16:32,330
[Relieved]

335
00:16:32,330 --> 00:16:36,860
Park So Rang and Go Hyeon Guk
will be in third place.

336
00:16:36,860 --> 00:16:39,650
[Team "Taste of Youth" is in fifth place
and in danger of elimination]

337
00:16:39,650 --> 00:16:42,140
What do you think? The average
viewing time isn't bad.

338
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:44,690
They finally got their smile back.

339
00:16:44,690 --> 00:16:46,060
What do you think, Director Park So Rang?

340
00:16:46,060 --> 00:16:50,200
When I saw the stop count, I thought
we wouldn't go past 100 seconds.

341
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:53,510
I kept praying that we get past 100 seconds.

342
00:16:53,510 --> 00:16:57,630
And we actually did. So, I'm happy now.

343
00:16:58,460 --> 00:16:59,860
I'm glad. What about you, Director Go?

344
00:16:59,860 --> 00:17:01,890
I'm so happy, too.

345
00:17:01,890 --> 00:17:06,360
We got a great result despite
the stop count. Thank you.

346
00:17:06,360 --> 00:17:07,830
Thank you.

347
00:17:07,830 --> 00:17:09,710
This is making me realize again.

348
00:17:09,710 --> 00:17:12,350
It's all about when people press the button.

349
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:16,440
Keun Suk just called it a seaweed
soup without sesame oil.

350
00:17:16,440 --> 00:17:19,820
But you keep eating it because it feels familiar.

351
00:17:19,820 --> 00:17:23,290
Some regions don't add sesame oil
to the seaweed soup.

352
00:17:23,290 --> 00:17:25,670
Some use perilla oil instead.

353
00:17:25,670 --> 00:17:29,040
Good work. Go back to your seats
and wait for the result.

354
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,770
Thank you.

355
00:17:30,770 --> 00:17:33,950
I think they are safe with 103 seconds.

356
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:36,490
Now, they'll get pushed down.

357
00:17:36,490 --> 00:17:38,190
[The result from now on will
determine elimination]

358
00:17:38,190 --> 00:17:42,200
The current first place,
Team "Black Out Girl Hanami"

359
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:45,800
and second place, Team "Meet My Roommate"

360
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:48,210
are advancing to the next round.

361
00:17:48,210 --> 00:17:50,930
The fate of the other three teams
will be determined

362
00:17:50,930 --> 00:17:53,600
by the remaining teams' results.

363
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,890
Let's meet the next team.

364
00:17:55,890 --> 00:18:01,270
I heard this team is competing with a master.

365
00:18:02,240 --> 00:18:04,200
[Already entertained]

366
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,870
I'm worried and excited at the same time.

367
00:18:06,870 --> 00:18:10,490
"Father's Home-Cooked Meal"
is about a husband who starts cooking

368
00:18:10,490 --> 00:18:13,530
after his wife forgets
how to cook after an accident.

369
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:17,100
Director Lee Joon Ik is working on this.

370
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:20,410
[Lee Joon Ik is directing a short drama,
"Father's Home-Cooked Meal"]

371
00:18:20,410 --> 00:18:23,820
They'll be compared to Director Lee Joon Ik.

372
00:18:23,820 --> 00:18:26,520
Wow, that's a lot of pressure.

373
00:18:26,520 --> 00:18:29,060
- We should avoid that one.
- That one's no good.

374
00:18:29,060 --> 00:18:31,370
Just avoid that one.

375
00:18:31,370 --> 00:18:34,260
[Everyone was tiptoeing around
after the six webtoons were taken]

376
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:38,000
We'll choose "Father's Home-Cooked Meal."

377
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:42,000
[Father's Home-Cooked Meal]

378
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,210
- It's Seo Jin Won.
- I like it.

379
00:18:44,210 --> 00:18:46,400
That's powerful.

380
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:47,770
Hello.

381
00:18:47,770 --> 00:18:49,820
Experienced Eun Jong Hun.

382
00:18:49,820 --> 00:18:51,550
The fighter, Jang Yu Jin.

383
00:18:51,550 --> 00:18:53,190
- With force...
- And spirit.

384
00:18:53,190 --> 00:18:55,730
- Force!
- Spirit?

385
00:18:55,730 --> 00:18:58,010
[They should've practiced]

386
00:18:58,010 --> 00:18:59,680
In the team introduction,

387
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:02,750
her exclamation point was met
with his question mark.

388
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:04,440
[Embarrassed]

389
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:08,120
I'm curious how you two worked together on set.

390
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:12,170
To be honest, I don't have much.

391
00:19:12,170 --> 00:19:16,170
I don't have much experience,
and I wasn't formally trained.

392
00:19:16,170 --> 00:19:18,490
I don't have connections or anything.

393
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:21,220
But Director Eun is experienced.

394
00:19:21,220 --> 00:19:25,060
He must've been good to those
around him. He has great connections.

395
00:19:25,060 --> 00:19:28,440
I worked on a film set for about 10 years.

396
00:19:28,440 --> 00:19:29,310
[Steven Yeun / Eun Jong Hun]

397
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:32,180
[He has worked on famous projects]

398
00:19:32,180 --> 00:19:35,000
[Seasoned director Eun Jong Hun]

399
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:38,000
Long time no see. Are you back from Mexico?

400
00:19:38,030 --> 00:19:40,430
Good to see you. Long time no see.
This is Han Wul.

401
00:19:40,430 --> 00:19:44,240
Long time no see.
Thank you for coming. Thank you.

402
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:48,140
We had about 25 people in the
film crew, excluding actors.

403
00:19:48,140 --> 00:19:52,550
I was fortunate that
they were willing to help me.

404
00:19:52,550 --> 00:19:54,890
I'm very thankful.

405
00:19:54,890 --> 00:19:57,810
[The scale is on another level!]

406
00:19:58,670 --> 00:20:03,480
[Props are being moved inside nonstop]

407
00:20:04,410 --> 00:20:07,230
[The house is already full!]

408
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:10,600
[There are tons of toys, too]

409
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:13,510
They brought all the props they have.

410
00:20:13,510 --> 00:20:19,410
There are scenes where we have
to show the change of time.

411
00:20:19,410 --> 00:20:23,020
We got ten years' worth of objects.

412
00:20:23,020 --> 00:20:24,860
Director Eun is the best.

413
00:20:24,860 --> 00:20:26,670
I chose him.

414
00:20:26,670 --> 00:20:28,200
I made a good choice.

415
00:20:28,970 --> 00:20:31,200
Ma'am.

416
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,580
We'll do a rehearsal first here.

417
00:20:33,580 --> 00:20:35,590
They'll run the entire movement flow.

418
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:36,900
Can you stand in the spot?

419
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:39,440
Since I'm an actress myself,

420
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:43,600
I focused on acting in general.

421
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:46,860
[Custom directing for child actors]

422
00:20:46,860 --> 00:20:50,220
"Wow! Pew, pew! Wow!" Stuff like this.

423
00:20:50,220 --> 00:20:52,360
You can do it, right?

424
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:55,890
Go, Roy! Pew, pew! Target detected.

425
00:20:55,890 --> 00:20:58,140
Pew, pew, pew! Shoot in the air.

426
00:20:58,140 --> 00:21:00,230
Pew, pew!

427
00:21:00,230 --> 00:21:02,160
Why am I tired?

428
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:04,130
[Energizing force, Jang Yu Jin]

429
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:05,780
[Next is the cooking scene]

430
00:21:05,780 --> 00:21:08,570
Scoop out the soybean paste like this. Garlic.

431
00:21:08,570 --> 00:21:10,830
Tofu. Right, tofu.

432
00:21:10,830 --> 00:21:12,610
Sorry.

433
00:21:12,610 --> 00:21:15,080
[Endless cooking hell]

434
00:21:16,190 --> 00:21:19,230
[What kind of dish will the father make?]

435
00:21:19,230 --> 00:21:24,530
You must've been concerned since
Lee Joon Ik is a master director.

436
00:21:24,530 --> 00:21:28,490
That's true, but I think Director Lee Joon Ik

437
00:21:28,490 --> 00:21:32,210
saw things from the father's perspective.

438
00:21:32,210 --> 00:21:35,950
I think we saw things
from the child's perspective.

439
00:21:35,950 --> 00:21:38,810
It will be fun to compare that difference.

440
00:21:38,810 --> 00:21:42,760
This might help promote Director Lee Joon Ik.

441
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:44,710
I suppose it could.

442
00:21:44,710 --> 00:21:46,710
- I think it could.
- I hope it does.

443
00:21:46,710 --> 00:21:48,120
Call me, sir.

444
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:49,180
[He supports them]

445
00:21:49,180 --> 00:21:54,040
I remember everyone was jealous
of your hidden item.

446
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:55,590
It must be this team.

447
00:21:56,670 --> 00:21:59,710
I'll reveal the hidden item.

448
00:21:59,710 --> 00:22:01,120
[Deadline delayed by a day]

449
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:03,510
[Wow]

450
00:22:03,510 --> 00:22:06,630
Wow, I've never been so jealous.

451
00:22:06,630 --> 00:22:08,380
I'm a bit jealous of that.

452
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:11,260
They get an extra 24 hours.

453
00:22:11,260 --> 00:22:15,250
We had an extra 24 hours,

454
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:18,070
but we only used four hours.

455
00:22:18,070 --> 00:22:20,340
We submitted it right away because

456
00:22:20,340 --> 00:22:23,740
we prefer not to be so close to the deadline.

457
00:22:23,740 --> 00:22:25,650
We're both like that.

458
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:28,360
We thought it would be better
to send it right away.

459
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:30,950
I hope you give us extra points.

460
00:22:30,950 --> 00:22:32,360
[Good pitch]

461
00:22:32,360 --> 00:22:34,120
Apparently, they can't.

462
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:36,230
What a waste of 20 hours.

463
00:22:36,230 --> 00:22:38,680
- We should have gotten that instead.
- I know, we should've.

464
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:41,450
The best short drama director told us

465
00:22:41,450 --> 00:22:44,680
about hook, turn, and cut.

466
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:48,730
But our hook is a bit different
than the usual kind.

467
00:22:48,730 --> 00:22:51,860
We tried to create an emotional hook.

468
00:22:51,860 --> 00:22:55,870
I hope that touches many people's hearts.

469
00:22:55,870 --> 00:22:57,930
They must've done a good job.

470
00:22:57,930 --> 00:22:59,960
I'm excited.

471
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:03,380
We'll get started. Play the video.

472
00:23:03,380 --> 00:23:06,100
["Father's Home-Cooked Meal"]

473
00:23:06,100 --> 00:23:08,490
[Jang Yu Jin and Eun Jong Hun's
"Father's Home-Cooked Meal"]

474
00:23:08,490 --> 00:23:12,990
As I remember, my mother was
always in the kitchen.

475
00:23:12,990 --> 00:23:17,620
She was the first one to wake up
to prepare breakfast for us.

476
00:23:17,620 --> 00:23:22,010
Right after doing the dishes, she started lunch.

477
00:23:22,010 --> 00:23:26,590
After clearing the lunch table,
she made snacks for us.

478
00:23:26,600 --> 00:23:32,100
She made dinner as the sun set.

479
00:23:32,100 --> 00:23:34,470
[The stop count starts]

480
00:23:35,040 --> 00:23:37,720
[It's rising quickly]

481
00:23:38,220 --> 00:23:40,870
I think the mom scene was too long.

482
00:23:40,870 --> 00:23:43,810
We spent too much time
on something too obvious.

483
00:23:43,810 --> 00:23:48,000
I wish we had spent a few seconds less.

484
00:23:48,850 --> 00:23:53,550
Father sat at the table for every single meal.

485
00:23:53,550 --> 00:23:58,260
He took the meals she prepared for granted.

486
00:24:02,260 --> 00:24:04,280
It's missing the onion.

487
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:06,730
It's missing the onion.

488
00:24:06,730 --> 00:24:10,870
[People are showing reactions]

489
00:24:10,870 --> 00:24:15,990
Mother never got upset because
she accepted it as normal.

490
00:24:15,990 --> 00:24:18,950
I thought it was normal, too.

491
00:24:19,840 --> 00:24:22,450
Gosh, seriously.

492
00:24:22,450 --> 00:24:25,330
No, don't do it.

493
00:24:25,330 --> 00:24:28,530
Gosh, please...

494
00:24:30,420 --> 00:24:33,650
But nothing should be taken for granted.

495
00:24:33,650 --> 00:24:36,840
Father shed tears for the first time that day.

496
00:24:36,840 --> 00:24:40,170
While peeling an onion for Mother.

497
00:24:41,320 --> 00:24:43,890
[The number goes up right
after the turning point]

498
00:24:43,890 --> 00:24:45,930
[Over 20 stops already]

499
00:24:45,930 --> 00:24:46,720
[Glancing]

500
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:49,450
Watching the number go up, I was like

501
00:24:49,450 --> 00:24:51,430
"No!"

502
00:24:51,430 --> 00:24:54,510
"Stop going up!" I kept thinking that.

503
00:24:54,510 --> 00:24:58,990
Father said that a man loses his
manhood if he works in the kitchen.

504
00:25:01,050 --> 00:25:03,270
He spent a long time in the kitchen,

505
00:25:03,270 --> 00:25:07,100
but fortunately, he never lost his manhood.

506
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:10,050
He successfully made soybean paste stew.

507
00:25:11,820 --> 00:25:13,470
[Mother is alive]

508
00:25:13,470 --> 00:25:15,660
[What a relief!]

509
00:25:15,660 --> 00:25:21,750
When she tasted his soybean paste
stew for the first time, she thought...

510
00:25:27,500 --> 00:25:29,280
You call this a soybean paste stew?

511
00:25:29,280 --> 00:25:30,510
[Shocked]

512
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:31,610
[LOL]

513
00:25:31,610 --> 00:25:33,340
[What a twist!]

514
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:39,790
You call this a soybean paste stew?

515
00:25:39,790 --> 00:25:41,810
It's Father's turn now.

516
00:25:41,810 --> 00:25:44,500
[You can watch the full version on Lehzin Snack]

517
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:46,330
What a powerful last scene.

518
00:25:46,330 --> 00:25:48,170
Redoing that scene would have been so annoying.

519
00:25:48,170 --> 00:25:49,650
That was good.

520
00:25:50,310 --> 00:25:52,970
Why is the count so high? They did a great job.

521
00:25:52,970 --> 00:25:56,080
You received 27 stops.

522
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:59,230
It's a bit of a disappointing number,

523
00:25:59,230 --> 00:26:02,200
but I think it turned out well.

524
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:04,630
I just find the result a bit disappointing.

525
00:26:04,630 --> 00:26:07,570
But I'll humbly accept it.

526
00:26:07,570 --> 00:26:12,270
We thought a lot about how
to transition from mother to father.

527
00:26:12,270 --> 00:26:16,840
We thought about our mothers
while working on this.

528
00:26:16,840 --> 00:26:21,730
I hope those emotions show through a bit.

529
00:26:21,730 --> 00:26:23,030
Thank you.

530
00:26:23,030 --> 00:26:25,980
It's time for harsh criticism.

531
00:26:25,980 --> 00:26:29,520
In the first scene,

532
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:32,500
the baby on the mother's back
was fake, wasn't it?

533
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:34,260
I have to agree with him.

534
00:26:34,260 --> 00:26:36,640
Yes, you're right.

535
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:39,840
[The baby has no weight to it]

536
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:43,230
[Deducted points immediately]

537
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:49,020
I think details like that can
make it feel less authentic.

538
00:26:49,020 --> 00:26:50,520
I was a bit disappointed with that.

539
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:52,600
I almost couldn't believe it.

540
00:26:52,600 --> 00:26:55,560
What was that, a rice pot?

541
00:26:55,560 --> 00:26:58,610
I was disappointed that you
didn't put any effort into it.

542
00:26:58,610 --> 00:27:02,030
You could've done something
during the extra 20 hours.

543
00:27:02,030 --> 00:27:03,540
They had an extra day.

544
00:27:03,540 --> 00:27:07,050
You boldly didn't use the 20 hours.

545
00:27:07,050 --> 00:27:09,850
You could have used that time to cast a baby.

546
00:27:09,850 --> 00:27:12,110
It's a bad thing they got an extra day.

547
00:27:12,110 --> 00:27:13,950
It was more of a handicap.

548
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:18,800
I'm most curious about what
Director Lee thought of it all.

549
00:27:18,820 --> 00:27:21,500
Do you think they followed your advice?

550
00:27:21,500 --> 00:27:24,360
- No.
- Huh?

551
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:26,710
[Failed to achieve hook, turn, and cut]

552
00:27:26,710 --> 00:27:29,290
You must've been very stressed about this.

553
00:27:29,290 --> 00:27:32,550
The sensibility of the original webtoon is

554
00:27:32,550 --> 00:27:34,870
already a handicap in short form.

555
00:27:34,870 --> 00:27:39,340
But I think this kind of work is
experimental in this field.

556
00:27:39,340 --> 00:27:41,970
We can't always talk about dopamine all the time.

557
00:27:41,970 --> 00:27:43,880
I think work like this could

558
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:47,620
introduce diversity in the field
to settle the market.

559
00:27:47,620 --> 00:27:51,790
I couldn't press the button for that reason.

560
00:27:51,790 --> 00:27:55,500
His comment felt like a tap on the shoulder.

561
00:27:55,500 --> 00:27:59,490
I found it to be encouraging and energizing.

562
00:27:59,490 --> 00:28:03,240
We'll have the first elimination now.

563
00:28:03,240 --> 00:28:05,840
- Is it happening now?
- Hold on, you're right.

564
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:08,030
[Five out of eight teams were judged]

565
00:28:09,110 --> 00:28:12,190
[The bottom three will be eliminated]

566
00:28:12,190 --> 00:28:14,490
[Depending on the result of
"Father's Home-Cooked Meal,"]

567
00:28:14,490 --> 00:28:17,540
[the sixth-place team will be eliminated!]

568
00:28:17,920 --> 00:28:20,240
[Which team will avoid elimination?]

569
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:23,240
- "Taste of Youth."
- They must be nervous.

570
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:24,900
How do you feel?

571
00:28:24,900 --> 00:28:27,820
We've let go of everything.

572
00:28:27,820 --> 00:28:29,470
We are ready to accept it.

573
00:28:29,470 --> 00:28:33,710
Do you think yours was better
than "Father's Home-Cooked Meal"?

574
00:28:33,710 --> 00:28:37,030
I don't think so. Ours were both about food,

575
00:28:37,030 --> 00:28:38,940
but they showed a greater variety of food.

576
00:28:38,940 --> 00:28:41,890
[We only saw takoyaki in "Taste of Youth"]

577
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:45,290
[We saw all kinds of food in
"Father's Home-Cooked Meal"]

578
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:47,960
Home-cooked meal or takoyaki?

579
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:51,300
Gosh, this is tough.

580
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:53,710
We are feeling nervous.

581
00:28:53,710 --> 00:28:56,470
We'll have the first elimination.

582
00:28:56,470 --> 00:29:02,880
Let's check the average viewing time
for "Father's Home-Cooked Meal."

583
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:05,460
Show us the result.

584
00:29:06,760 --> 00:29:09,920
The stop count was 27.

585
00:29:09,920 --> 00:29:13,540
I hope it's at least 90 seconds. Please.

586
00:29:13,540 --> 00:29:15,970
I have a bad feeling.

587
00:29:15,970 --> 00:29:20,890
Will it be higher than 81.54?

588
00:29:20,890 --> 00:29:23,320
31 stops, right? But you never know.

589
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:26,270
I don't think they'll be eliminated.

590
00:29:26,270 --> 00:29:29,070
[Nerve-racking moment]

591
00:29:29,070 --> 00:29:31,460
It was so unpredictable.

592
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:38,070
[Oh? Wow!]

593
00:29:38,070 --> 00:29:39,820
[Daebak]

594
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:42,490
[Average viewing time - 87.52 seconds]

595
00:29:42,490 --> 00:29:45,070
[Did we win?]

596
00:29:45,620 --> 00:29:47,160
[Devastated]

597
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,700
They aren't in fifth place.

598
00:29:49,700 --> 00:29:51,900
They are in fourth place.

599
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:55,120
Wow, fourth place. That's pretty good.

600
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:57,310
[They are being eliminated]

601
00:29:57,310 --> 00:30:02,890
It means the stop votes came in late.

602
00:30:02,890 --> 00:30:05,590
That was a very slim difference.

603
00:30:05,590 --> 00:30:07,830
We'll continue to work hard,

604
00:30:07,830 --> 00:30:10,290
but I hope we get to survive.

605
00:30:10,290 --> 00:30:11,970
[There are two teams left]

606
00:30:11,970 --> 00:30:15,240
We'll watch the rest happily.

607
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:17,270
Good work, Team "Father's Home-Cooked Meal."

608
00:30:17,270 --> 00:30:21,240
With the average viewing time of 87.52 seconds,

609
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:23,710
you're in fourth place. Good job.

610
00:30:23,710 --> 00:30:29,300
Good thing we got people to watch
for a minute and a half.

611
00:30:29,300 --> 00:30:33,160
Is Team "Taste of Youth" being eliminated?

612
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:36,240
[Apparently so...]

613
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:39,880
Do we make them leave right away?

614
00:30:41,550 --> 00:30:43,700
- Are they really leaving?
- Really?

615
00:30:43,700 --> 00:30:46,440
They must be curious about how others will do.

616
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:48,130
They still have to vote.

617
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:53,300
If you start voting randomly just
because you were eliminated,

618
00:30:53,340 --> 00:30:56,520
- we'll know it was you.
- Darn it!

619
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:59,440
As you know, the voting isn't
totally confidential.

620
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:01,980
[Vote in good conscience]

621
00:31:01,980 --> 00:31:05,010
[The top three teams are
advancing to the next round]

622
00:31:05,010 --> 00:31:07,690
[Seo Jun Gyo and Kwon Sun Yong
are being eliminated]

623
00:31:08,080 --> 00:31:11,040
[The 4th and 5th place teams can't relax yet]

624
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:14,440
[The elimination depends on the
result of the last two teams]

625
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:17,920
[At the crossroads of fate]

626
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:20,970
[Which two teams will have the last laugh?]

627
00:31:20,970 --> 00:31:25,250
Round 2 became more competitive
after the first elimination.

628
00:31:25,250 --> 00:31:27,890
Let's quickly meet the next team.

629
00:31:27,890 --> 00:31:31,390
This team kind of...

630
00:31:31,390 --> 00:31:34,440
reminds you of "Beauty and the Beast."

631
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:36,910
[Which webtoon did Yang Gyeong Hee
and Yun Hyeong Shik choose?]

632
00:31:36,910 --> 00:31:38,250
["You're Falling from the Sky"]

633
00:31:38,250 --> 00:31:41,500
"You're Falling from the Sky."

634
00:31:41,500 --> 00:31:43,460
I conquered the web drama industry.

635
00:31:43,460 --> 00:31:45,490
I conquered the short-form industry in America.

636
00:31:45,490 --> 00:31:47,810
Now, we are here to conquer Director's Arena.

637
00:31:47,810 --> 00:31:49,630
- I'm Yang Gyeong Hee.
- I'm Yun Hyeong Shik.

638
00:31:49,630 --> 00:31:51,800
We're Team "You're Falling from the Sky."

639
00:31:51,800 --> 00:31:53,440
[So cute]

640
00:31:53,440 --> 00:31:55,330
They practiced a lot.

641
00:31:56,150 --> 00:31:57,740
So good.

642
00:31:57,740 --> 00:31:59,720
[Embarrassed]

643
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:05,530
You've both been acknowledged for your talent.

644
00:32:05,530 --> 00:32:08,660
[Timeslip rom-com, "Joseon Man, MZ Woman"]

645
00:32:08,660 --> 00:32:10,260
Time flew by again.

646
00:32:10,260 --> 00:32:12,250
[Survived Round 1 in eighth place]

647
00:32:12,250 --> 00:32:15,390
I've directed two short dramas outside of Korea.

648
00:32:15,390 --> 00:32:17,490
Your resume is so impressive.

649
00:32:17,490 --> 00:32:22,920
I directed "Medical Genius" and "Beyond the Law."

650
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:25,600
[A team of a Korean and
an international director]

651
00:32:25,600 --> 00:32:29,080
Did you have any disagreements while directing?

652
00:32:29,080 --> 00:32:31,380
I learned we're both a bit impatient.

653
00:32:31,380 --> 00:32:34,000
So, we made decisions very quickly.

654
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:36,570
He accepted my opinions generously.

655
00:32:36,570 --> 00:32:40,530
And I liked the feedback he provided, too.

656
00:32:40,530 --> 00:32:47,080
I first realized that working
as a team could create synergy.

657
00:32:47,080 --> 00:32:50,540
You are impatient and make decisions quickly.

658
00:32:50,540 --> 00:32:53,780
But I heard you were short on editing time.

659
00:32:53,780 --> 00:32:57,500
Well, our story is set in high school.

660
00:32:57,500 --> 00:32:59,760
The lead characters are in 11th grade.

661
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:03,540
We were only able to rent a school on weekends.

662
00:33:03,540 --> 00:33:07,830
In the first week, we were busy with casting.

663
00:33:07,830 --> 00:33:11,950
We only got to film in Week 2, but that
was two days before the deadline.

664
00:33:11,950 --> 00:33:13,100
[What a shame]

665
00:33:13,100 --> 00:33:14,920
So, we finished in a rush.

666
00:33:14,920 --> 00:33:18,530
You must've had a long preparation
period since you filmed late.

667
00:33:18,530 --> 00:33:20,360
- That's right.
- Then...

668
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:24,940
what did you pay extra
attention to while filming?

669
00:33:24,940 --> 00:33:29,590
The original webtoon is very poetic.

670
00:33:29,590 --> 00:33:33,250
The characters don't experience love

671
00:33:33,250 --> 00:33:38,270
because of the romance suppressant called LS.

672
00:33:38,270 --> 00:33:43,620
But the male lead, Lee Do, meets
Bo Reum Chan and falls in love.

673
00:33:43,620 --> 00:33:47,630
The story is set during a rainy period.

674
00:33:47,630 --> 00:33:51,720
It starts raining the moment Lee Do
meets Han Bo Reum Chan.

675
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:55,600
Han Bo Reum Chan represents the rain.

676
00:33:55,600 --> 00:34:01,110
We wanted to capture the romantic
sensibility using rain.

677
00:34:01,110 --> 00:34:03,150
We focused on that while directing.

678
00:34:03,150 --> 00:34:07,280
In summary, first love comes
to you like the rain.

679
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:09,460
[Cherry blossoms are in full bloom on set]

680
00:34:10,050 --> 00:34:12,850
[Unfamiliar feeling in the world without love]

681
00:34:13,390 --> 00:34:14,660
Rain.

682
00:34:15,430 --> 00:34:17,290
Go. Be on the way.

683
00:34:17,290 --> 00:34:19,630
Ready. Action.

684
00:34:19,630 --> 00:34:21,710
[Love will fall like the rain in this dry world]

685
00:34:22,290 --> 00:34:26,450
[How did they depict this new worldview?]

686
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,680
I wore shoes that don't match.

687
00:34:29,680 --> 00:34:30,650
[Laugh]

688
00:34:30,650 --> 00:34:32,960
- From where? From home?
- Yes, I was so out of it.

689
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,850
- This is a trend these days.
- No, it isn't.

690
00:34:34,850 --> 00:34:37,940
People do that on purpose. I'm serious.

691
00:34:37,940 --> 00:34:39,630
It's Hannam-dong style.

692
00:34:39,630 --> 00:34:42,460
Is it Hannam-dong style?

693
00:34:42,460 --> 00:34:46,290
I'm usually not like this.
This is my first time ever.

694
00:34:46,290 --> 00:34:49,050
I swear I've never done this before.

695
00:34:49,050 --> 00:34:50,540
[Directing in unmatched shoes]

696
00:34:50,540 --> 00:34:53,770
I am in charge of props and locations.

697
00:34:53,770 --> 00:34:55,980
You're feeling comforted as you touch hands.

698
00:34:55,980 --> 00:34:58,080
[Directing emotions in detail]

699
00:34:58,080 --> 00:35:01,820
[Director Yang Gyeong Hee: Directing,
emotions, wrong shoes, props]

700
00:35:01,820 --> 00:35:05,810
Director Yun was in charge
of production in general.

701
00:35:06,940 --> 00:35:08,880
[Getting costumes, too]

702
00:35:08,880 --> 00:35:11,190
[Director Yun Hyeong Shik: Assistant director,
does everything he's asked, runs the set]

703
00:35:11,460 --> 00:35:13,100
[The important downpour scene]

704
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:15,110
Breathe. Breathe more. Breathe more.

705
00:35:15,110 --> 00:35:17,870
[The actors' emotions are
important in this drama]

706
00:35:18,460 --> 00:35:20,850
[Focusing on directing instead
of the mismatched shoes]

707
00:35:20,850 --> 00:35:23,510
Cut. That scene didn't work at all.

708
00:35:23,510 --> 00:35:26,650
Don't they look too small on the screen?

709
00:35:26,650 --> 00:35:28,410
We'll start with the two of them together.

710
00:35:28,410 --> 00:35:30,150
We can start with the reflection.

711
00:35:30,150 --> 00:35:31,820
Excuse me. Gosh.

712
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:34,740
[Make it happen no matter what]

713
00:35:34,740 --> 00:35:36,420
[Yun Hyeong Shik makes things happen]

714
00:35:36,420 --> 00:35:38,270
[Flawless teamwork]

715
00:35:38,270 --> 00:35:42,440
I help realize Director Yang's vision.

716
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:44,580
I'm in charge of production.

717
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:47,500
I was too busy making the scenes happen.

718
00:35:47,500 --> 00:35:50,560
I hope Director Yang was satisfied with it.

719
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:51,700
Cut.

720
00:35:51,700 --> 00:35:53,900
- Cut.
- Cut, okay.

721
00:35:53,900 --> 00:35:55,580
[Director Yun is all over the set!]

722
00:35:56,100 --> 00:35:58,130
[Running out of breath]

723
00:35:58,130 --> 00:36:00,340
Things moved along without me saying anything.

724
00:36:00,340 --> 00:36:02,600
[Working in perfect harmony
while battling with time]

725
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:04,420
[Director Yun Hyeong Shik has logged out]

726
00:36:04,420 --> 00:36:05,600
[Recharging for a moment]

727
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:09,210
[Director Yang is picking up someone]

728
00:36:09,210 --> 00:36:12,500
Back in the day,

729
00:36:12,500 --> 00:36:16,790
he appeared in a short film I directed.

730
00:36:16,790 --> 00:36:19,860
That's how we know each other well.

731
00:36:19,860 --> 00:36:21,810
Hello.

732
00:36:23,230 --> 00:36:25,660
[The person she ran out to welcome]

733
00:36:26,460 --> 00:36:29,900
[Secret weapon for "You're Falling from the Sky"]

734
00:36:30,680 --> 00:36:34,050
Hello, I'm actor Jo Deok Hyeon.

735
00:36:34,050 --> 00:36:36,330
I'm playing the doctor.

736
00:36:36,330 --> 00:36:39,180
Ready, action.

737
00:36:40,910 --> 00:36:44,120
She's good at drawing out actors' emotions.

738
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:48,300
I think she's very seasoned for her age.

739
00:36:48,300 --> 00:36:52,140
We need to nurture directors like her.

740
00:36:52,140 --> 00:36:54,030
Fighting.

741
00:36:54,830 --> 00:36:56,500
Gosh, thank you.

742
00:36:56,500 --> 00:36:58,460
That was a lie.

743
00:36:58,460 --> 00:37:00,360
[Everyone is in perfect harmony on this set]

744
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:03,400
I'm telling you.

745
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:05,900
I'm not the good person you think I am.

746
00:37:05,930 --> 00:37:08,220
Remember to breathe.

747
00:37:08,220 --> 00:37:11,070
[The drama is coming together in full efficiency]

748
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:15,900
[We are excited to watch
"You're Falling from the Sky"]

749
00:37:16,600 --> 00:37:24,000
I'm curious how you told the story
in what style within two minutes.

750
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:29,400
We both worked hard on making it sentimental.

751
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:34,770
I think that will be the key point.

752
00:37:34,770 --> 00:37:37,660
It's a poetic and slow-paced webtoon.

753
00:37:37,660 --> 00:37:41,450
I think we did everything with an intention.

754
00:37:41,450 --> 00:37:44,580
Even if it's not received well,

755
00:37:44,580 --> 00:37:47,230
I don't think I'll have a lot of regrets.

756
00:37:47,230 --> 00:37:49,780
["You're Falling from the Sky"]

757
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:52,560
We are not able to love.

758
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:57,250
The late Dr. Kim Seok Hwan developed
a romance suppressant for students.

759
00:37:57,250 --> 00:38:00,140
The government administered that to us.

760
00:38:00,920 --> 00:38:04,440
I find that to be such a relief.

761
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:07,150
But why...

762
00:38:20,250 --> 00:38:22,410
Lee Do,

763
00:38:22,410 --> 00:38:24,640
my dog...

764
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,910
died.

765
00:38:27,910 --> 00:38:30,590
Lee Do, do you like dogs?

766
00:38:30,590 --> 00:38:32,510
I've had a dog since I was a kid.

767
00:38:32,510 --> 00:38:34,330
The romance suppressant, LS.

768
00:38:34,330 --> 00:38:35,950
Does it have side effects?

769
00:38:35,950 --> 00:38:39,160
There aren't any known cases yet,

770
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:41,870
but it has potential for it.

771
00:38:43,330 --> 00:38:47,340
[Is it the pacing? The stop count keeps going up]

772
00:38:47,340 --> 00:38:49,630
[No reaction is more cruel than harsh criticism]

773
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:52,540
We think of it as a breather,

774
00:38:52,540 --> 00:38:56,500
but the viewers could have
found that part a bit slow.

775
00:38:56,500 --> 00:39:04,000
That's when I realized that the viewers
might have found it too forced.

776
00:39:04,030 --> 00:39:07,720
[Forced emotions don't come through]

777
00:39:17,420 --> 00:39:18,930
Thank you, Lee Do.

778
00:39:18,930 --> 00:39:20,640
You don't have to thank me.

779
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:22,730
I'm not usually like that.

780
00:39:22,730 --> 00:39:25,870
You're a good person to me.

781
00:39:25,870 --> 00:39:27,200
Aren't you?

782
00:39:27,870 --> 00:39:29,730
Who do you think you are?

783
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:32,460
I'm telling you.

784
00:39:32,460 --> 00:39:35,330
I'm not the good person you think I am.

785
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:42,560
Lee Do.

786
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:45,520
Even after being administered with LS,

787
00:39:45,520 --> 00:39:49,330
if you still get romantic feelings,

788
00:39:50,510 --> 00:39:51,820
[Can't focus]

789
00:39:51,820 --> 00:39:57,000
those feelings will clash
with the LS within the system

790
00:39:57,000 --> 00:40:00,150
and it could lead to death.

791
00:40:00,150 --> 00:40:02,350
I hate rain.

792
00:40:05,080 --> 00:40:07,650
Rain brings rain clouds

793
00:40:10,020 --> 00:40:12,340
and ruins everything.

794
00:40:13,140 --> 00:40:14,900
["You're Falling from the Sky" got 25 stops]

795
00:40:15,590 --> 00:40:18,790
[Disappointing score, more stop
counts than love feelings]

796
00:40:18,790 --> 00:40:21,720
When I first heard the plot,

797
00:40:21,720 --> 00:40:25,410
I was very curious.

798
00:40:25,410 --> 00:40:28,120
But I became less curious as I was watching.

799
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:31,290
I think I got that sense a bit.

800
00:40:31,290 --> 00:40:35,760
I'm not sure if it was the acting or directing.

801
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:39,470
I was hoping it would be more upbeat and fun,

802
00:40:39,470 --> 00:40:41,730
but it wasn't.

803
00:40:41,730 --> 00:40:44,410
It was so disappointing.

804
00:40:44,410 --> 00:40:46,590
I could be saying something similar.

805
00:40:46,590 --> 00:40:52,260
There was no way for me to tell
that this was a sad story.

806
00:40:52,260 --> 00:40:55,180
I found the plot itself so interesting.

807
00:40:55,180 --> 00:40:56,990
It's a bit of a fantasy.

808
00:40:56,990 --> 00:41:01,390
But it was very slow, unlike the plot.
Although I get the intention.

809
00:41:01,390 --> 00:41:04,800
But the viewers don't get any of the information.

810
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:07,670
The problem was that the genre was unclear.

811
00:41:07,670 --> 00:41:12,880
It should've been either a thriller or a romance.

812
00:41:12,880 --> 00:41:16,590
I think it had a bit of an identity crisis.

813
00:41:16,590 --> 00:41:19,900
This is a teen romance. It's a genre.

814
00:41:19,900 --> 00:41:23,360
But I think they neglected that part.

815
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:25,000
It was a shame.

816
00:41:26,300 --> 00:41:29,290
They didn't say they liked it or enjoyed it.

817
00:41:29,290 --> 00:41:33,540
Those were the criticisms I could accept.

818
00:41:33,540 --> 00:41:37,270
It made me reflect as a director.

819
00:41:38,120 --> 00:41:41,080
Directors Yang Gyeong Hee
and Yun Hyeong Shik's

820
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,730
"You're Falling from The Sky."

821
00:41:42,730 --> 00:41:46,920
Let's check the result.

822
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:50,730
You received 25 stops.

823
00:41:50,730 --> 00:41:53,520
Let's see what your average viewing time is.

824
00:41:53,520 --> 00:41:55,230
The current fifth-place team,

825
00:41:55,230 --> 00:41:57,990
Kim Dong Ha and Oh Hae On's team.

826
00:41:57,990 --> 00:42:01,480
Team "After School" must be feeling nervous.

827
00:42:01,480 --> 00:42:03,570
86.83 seconds.

828
00:42:03,570 --> 00:42:08,990
- What could it be?
- Let's reveal the result now.

829
00:42:08,990 --> 00:42:11,400
[The sixth-place team will
automatically be eliminated]

830
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:13,890
[Team "You're Falling from the Sky"
was all about sentimentality]

831
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:17,400
[Stop counts flooded in
due to a lack of dopamine]

832
00:42:18,760 --> 00:42:22,180
[But the average viewing time is crucial]

833
00:42:24,630 --> 00:42:26,640
Director Yang and I talked about this.

834
00:42:26,640 --> 00:42:30,050
We thought we'd be in fifth or sixth place.

835
00:42:30,050 --> 00:42:32,930
We thought we'd be fighting for one spot.

836
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:37,620
My hands were shaky, and my heart was racing.

837
00:42:38,490 --> 00:42:41,790
[The stop count for "After School" was
paused at the one-minute mark]

838
00:42:43,150 --> 00:42:47,690
I think we can aim for a good result.

839
00:42:47,690 --> 00:42:51,360
[The two teams are only one stop
away from each other]

840
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:54,320
Please reveal the number.

841
00:42:54,320 --> 00:42:58,490
[The sixth-place team will be eliminated]

842
00:43:00,120 --> 00:43:02,050
[Average viewing time - 95.60 seconds]

843
00:43:02,050 --> 00:43:03,680
That's pretty high.

844
00:43:03,680 --> 00:43:06,890
[Landing in fourth place]

845
00:43:06,890 --> 00:43:08,700
[Barely made it]

846
00:43:09,310 --> 00:43:12,810
[Team "You're Falling from the Sky" survives]

847
00:43:13,170 --> 00:43:16,450
[Team "After School" is being eliminated]

848
00:43:16,910 --> 00:43:18,750
[Finally able to relax]

849
00:43:18,750 --> 00:43:21,010
He's finally sending heart symbols.

850
00:43:21,880 --> 00:43:23,550
I can tell you this now.

851
00:43:23,550 --> 00:43:25,960
You can hear an anchorman's
voice halfway through.

852
00:43:25,960 --> 00:43:29,940
My elementary school friend,
anchorman Oh Se Hyuk, helped us.

853
00:43:29,940 --> 00:43:32,470
- I knew it.
- He has a nice voice.

854
00:43:32,470 --> 00:43:35,670
Thank you, Se Hyuk. You saved us.

855
00:43:35,670 --> 00:43:40,390
Actor Jo Deok Hyeon made
a special appearance, too.

856
00:43:40,390 --> 00:43:44,330
- I would like to thank him, too.
- Good work.

857
00:43:44,330 --> 00:43:49,510
Please return to your seats
and watch the results.

858
00:43:49,510 --> 00:43:53,340
What a shame. Directors Kim Dong Ha and Oh Hae On

859
00:43:53,340 --> 00:43:56,200
are in sixth place and will be eliminated.

860
00:43:56,200 --> 00:44:00,420
It was a team I was rooting for.

861
00:44:00,420 --> 00:44:03,890
- Like a dad.
- Please tell us how you feel.

862
00:44:03,890 --> 00:44:06,930
I'm so happy that we got this far.

863
00:44:06,930 --> 00:44:10,170
It's too bad that we can't show more of our work.

864
00:44:10,170 --> 00:44:14,090
But we'll show you that we improved next time.

865
00:44:14,090 --> 00:44:15,880
So eloquent.

866
00:44:15,880 --> 00:44:19,570
It was an honor to be on the show at all.

867
00:44:19,570 --> 00:44:24,500
I was so happy when we survived
Round 1, and I still am.

868
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:27,370
But the fact that we got eliminated...

869
00:44:28,720 --> 00:44:32,880
Just think about the older directors
who got eliminated in Round 1.

870
00:44:32,880 --> 00:44:34,570
Remember Director Seo Seong Won?

871
00:44:34,570 --> 00:44:37,650
People in their 30s and 40s can't do this,
but they are in middle school.

872
00:44:37,650 --> 00:44:40,200
You are so impressive.

873
00:44:40,200 --> 00:44:42,560
Thank you so much.

874
00:44:42,560 --> 00:44:48,230
It was so fun that we got
to play in this big pool.

875
00:44:48,230 --> 00:44:51,750
I really had a lot of fun.

876
00:44:51,750 --> 00:44:53,280
The future of short drama is bright.

877
00:44:53,280 --> 00:44:56,160
Director Kim Dong Ha, good work.

878
00:44:56,160 --> 00:44:59,680
I find this experience very motivating.

879
00:44:59,680 --> 00:45:03,150
It was meaningful for me personally.

880
00:45:03,150 --> 00:45:05,340
I had fun.

881
00:45:05,340 --> 00:45:08,370
You made valuable connections on the show.

882
00:45:08,370 --> 00:45:11,010
Thank you. It was a good drama.

883
00:45:11,010 --> 00:45:15,030
One last team is either facing
survival or elimination.

884
00:45:15,030 --> 00:45:20,250
Round 1's first-place Lee Yoo Jin
and third-place Han Soo Ji.

885
00:45:20,250 --> 00:45:22,250
They're potential winners.

886
00:45:22,250 --> 00:45:25,000
Let's check out what they prepared for us.

887
00:45:25,000 --> 00:45:27,640
[Revealing the thumbnail first]

888
00:45:28,130 --> 00:45:30,260
"Do Ri, Do Shim."

889
00:45:30,260 --> 00:45:32,350
[Everyone is focused on it!]

890
00:45:32,350 --> 00:45:34,770
I like that image.

891
00:45:34,770 --> 00:45:38,220
The webtoon we chose is "Do Ri, Do Shim."

892
00:45:38,220 --> 00:45:44,280
"Do Ri, Do Shim" is about a boy
who accidentally asks out a popular girl.

893
00:45:44,280 --> 00:45:46,290
That's intriguing.

894
00:45:46,290 --> 00:45:48,300
Amy. Isn't that Amy?

895
00:45:48,300 --> 00:45:53,120
- It is.
- She was their hidden item.

896
00:45:53,120 --> 00:45:55,290
[8.8 million followers]

897
00:45:58,390 --> 00:46:03,690
[Mega influencer, Amy, with various contents]

898
00:46:04,240 --> 00:46:07,330
This was her acting debut.

899
00:46:07,330 --> 00:46:13,160
[She posted a spoiler on social media]

900
00:46:14,360 --> 00:46:17,230
It was powerful. Amy is in it, too.

901
00:46:17,230 --> 00:46:19,110
It grabbed my eyes.

902
00:46:19,110 --> 00:46:21,600
This is one of the teams I was excited about.

903
00:46:21,600 --> 00:46:24,520
You are the last team. Thank you for waiting.

904
00:46:24,520 --> 00:46:26,860
Please introduce your team first.

905
00:46:26,860 --> 00:46:28,160
We have a team chant.

906
00:46:28,160 --> 00:46:29,670
Okay, okay.

907
00:46:29,670 --> 00:46:31,230
[Focused]

908
00:46:31,230 --> 00:46:33,620
- Yoo Jin.
- Soo Ji.

909
00:46:36,680 --> 00:46:38,130
Yoo Jin, Soo Ji.

910
00:46:38,130 --> 00:46:40,820
That's your slogan?

911
00:46:40,820 --> 00:46:43,780
You could've just told us the team name.

912
00:46:43,780 --> 00:46:45,290
I'm sorry.

913
00:46:45,290 --> 00:46:47,440
[I'm kidding]

914
00:46:47,440 --> 00:46:50,310
[Flustered]

915
00:46:50,310 --> 00:46:53,810
Is your team chant in short form on purpose?

916
00:46:53,900 --> 00:46:59,000
"Do Ri, Do Shim" is about Dol and Do Shim.

917
00:46:59,060 --> 00:47:01,760
- That's why we said Yoo Jin...
- Soo Ji.

918
00:47:01,760 --> 00:47:03,960
- That was the intention.
- I'm sorry.

919
00:47:03,960 --> 00:47:05,660
I didn't realize.

920
00:47:05,660 --> 00:47:08,890
[Round 1's first-place director, Lee Yoo Jin]

921
00:47:08,890 --> 00:47:12,910
[They are clearly the strongest team of Round 2]

922
00:47:12,910 --> 00:47:15,900
[Does this mean they'll win Round 2, as well?]

923
00:47:17,010 --> 00:47:19,510
[Lee Yoo Jin won first place with zero stops]

924
00:47:19,510 --> 00:47:21,170
"Snakes and Ladders."

925
00:47:21,170 --> 00:47:23,010
[Teaser for "Snakes and Ladders"
was on another level]

926
00:47:23,010 --> 00:47:26,360
[It was everyone's favorite thriller!]

927
00:47:26,360 --> 00:47:29,260
The person I want to work with is...

928
00:47:29,260 --> 00:47:31,190
Director Han Soo Ji.

929
00:47:32,320 --> 00:47:35,280
[This is how the short drama Avengers were born]

930
00:47:35,280 --> 00:47:36,920
You must be under a lot of pressure.

931
00:47:36,920 --> 00:47:39,210
How do you feel? You're the last team.

932
00:47:39,210 --> 00:47:41,860
I'm feeling a lot of pressure.

933
00:47:41,860 --> 00:47:44,760
I loved working with her because

934
00:47:44,760 --> 00:47:50,580
whenever I brought up something
that I thought might be too much,

935
00:47:50,580 --> 00:47:52,890
she already thought about it.

936
00:47:52,890 --> 00:47:55,490
She was like, "Of course, we have to do that."

937
00:47:55,490 --> 00:47:58,850
You're saying you're too much,
but she's even worse.

938
00:47:58,850 --> 00:48:00,310
Yes, yes.

939
00:48:00,400 --> 00:48:05,580
While working with him,
I became a bit scared of him.

940
00:48:05,580 --> 00:48:06,890
Scared? How...

941
00:48:06,890 --> 00:48:11,370
I learned how ambitious
he is while working together.

942
00:48:11,370 --> 00:48:16,380
I was relieved that we teamed up together.

943
00:48:16,380 --> 00:48:22,440
You can say Director's Arena is
a competition show in a nutshell.

944
00:48:22,500 --> 00:48:27,470
But when they teamed up, it suddenly
became like a dating show.

945
00:48:27,470 --> 00:48:29,900
[The eye candy director couple]

946
00:48:29,900 --> 00:48:32,340
[We're in bromance, too]

947
00:48:32,340 --> 00:48:35,210
I heard they met every single day.

948
00:48:35,210 --> 00:48:37,500
That's the rumor.

949
00:48:37,500 --> 00:48:39,610
- Is it true?
- Explain yourselves.

950
00:48:39,610 --> 00:48:41,480
Yes, it's true.

951
00:48:41,480 --> 00:48:44,330
We don't care about the result.

952
00:48:44,330 --> 00:48:45,810
This is more fun.

953
00:48:45,810 --> 00:48:48,250
- The romance that brews.
- What's going on?

954
00:48:48,250 --> 00:48:50,150
What a beautiful young couple.

955
00:48:50,150 --> 00:48:54,770
Since the day after Round 1,

956
00:48:54,770 --> 00:48:56,780
without missing a day,

957
00:48:56,780 --> 00:49:02,280
I visited her studio from Yangju.

958
00:49:02,280 --> 00:49:04,100
I liked it.

959
00:49:04,100 --> 00:49:05,780
"I liked it?"

960
00:49:05,780 --> 00:49:07,400
What did you like about it?

961
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:09,650
You probably didn't have separate roles.

962
00:49:09,700 --> 00:49:13,200
You were just attached to each other
and got lovey-dovey.

963
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:16,470
Hold on, I think you are mocking them right now.

964
00:49:16,470 --> 00:49:18,600
"These two are all lovey-dovey..."

965
00:49:18,600 --> 00:49:21,150
[What was their film set like?]

966
00:49:21,640 --> 00:49:23,880
[Spring came to Director's Arena]

967
00:49:23,880 --> 00:49:25,820
[Something is going on]

968
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:28,340
[Lovey-dovey]

969
00:49:28,340 --> 00:49:29,730
- Nice.
- Yay.

970
00:49:29,730 --> 00:49:33,380
[They can't stop laughing]

971
00:49:33,380 --> 00:49:37,130
[What exactly brought them closer?]

972
00:49:37,730 --> 00:49:40,690
[A few days before the shoot]

973
00:49:41,080 --> 00:49:44,290
[Their first meeting
after the filming of Round 1]

974
00:49:44,290 --> 00:49:46,880
- Avengers.
- Avengers.

975
00:49:46,880 --> 00:49:48,460
Let's go up.

976
00:49:48,460 --> 00:49:51,820
Let's share the ideas we came up with.

977
00:49:51,820 --> 00:49:54,400
I assume our picks are similar.

978
00:49:54,400 --> 00:49:56,420
That's what I think, too.

979
00:49:56,420 --> 00:49:58,850
- They're similar as I expected.
- I know, right?

980
00:49:58,850 --> 00:50:01,940
- They're basically the same.
- Right? I knew you'd want this, too.

981
00:50:01,940 --> 00:50:04,230
I love it.

982
00:50:04,230 --> 00:50:07,090
[In perfect sync]

983
00:50:08,160 --> 00:50:10,940
The flowers and the weather are so nice.

984
00:50:10,940 --> 00:50:12,630
[Director Han Soo Ji is
prepping for the shoot alone]

985
00:50:12,630 --> 00:50:14,760
We'll add the insert here.

986
00:50:14,760 --> 00:50:17,920
[Where is Director Lee Yoo Jin?]

987
00:50:17,920 --> 00:50:20,460
[Lee Yoo Jin plays the male lead, Dol]

988
00:50:20,460 --> 00:50:23,450
I have to look like a doormat.

989
00:50:23,450 --> 00:50:25,680
But I look too good in the uniform.

990
00:50:26,530 --> 00:50:29,140
You came. You came.

991
00:50:29,930 --> 00:50:31,460
You look like a doormat today.

992
00:50:31,460 --> 00:50:33,490
- I love it.
- Hello.

993
00:50:33,490 --> 00:50:35,460
Hello.

994
00:50:35,460 --> 00:50:37,870
[Someone else came to the set]

995
00:50:37,870 --> 00:50:39,340
- You look so pretty.
- I don't.

996
00:50:39,340 --> 00:50:42,190
She's so pretty. So pretty.

997
00:50:42,190 --> 00:50:44,770
This is actress Lee Soo Min.

998
00:50:44,770 --> 00:50:47,690
Hello, I'm Lee Soo Min.

999
00:50:47,690 --> 00:50:50,200
[She plays Dol's first love, Hye Jin]

1000
00:50:50,200 --> 00:50:53,590
[Breaking away from the dating show,
back to the shooting mode]

1001
00:50:53,590 --> 00:50:55,330
Action.

1002
00:50:56,280 --> 00:50:58,760
I heard you caught a cold.

1003
00:50:58,760 --> 00:51:01,170
Here's some porridge.

1004
00:51:01,170 --> 00:51:03,230
I asked Yeong Ja...

1005
00:51:03,230 --> 00:51:04,670
[Hurt]

1006
00:51:05,050 --> 00:51:07,640
Wake up and smell the coffee.

1007
00:51:07,640 --> 00:51:11,050
Why would a pretty girl like me date you?

1008
00:51:11,050 --> 00:51:13,680
You're less than my foot towel.

1009
00:51:16,340 --> 00:51:20,200
[Huge teardrops falling]

1010
00:51:21,090 --> 00:51:24,190
[Impressed]

1011
00:51:28,670 --> 00:51:31,690
Cut. I love it. I love it.

1012
00:51:31,690 --> 00:51:32,770
[The hidden actor, Amy, is here]

1013
00:51:32,770 --> 00:51:36,120
- Welcome.
- Hello.

1014
00:51:36,120 --> 00:51:37,860
Do Shim is here.

1015
00:51:38,660 --> 00:51:40,400
I'm so nervous right now.

1016
00:51:40,400 --> 00:51:42,270
But I'm so happy.

1017
00:51:42,270 --> 00:51:44,810
I didn't think I'd become Do Shim.

1018
00:51:44,810 --> 00:51:46,560
She's amazingly passionate.

1019
00:51:46,560 --> 00:51:48,250
She is exactly like the character.

1020
00:51:48,250 --> 00:51:50,610
She does exactly what the artist intended.

1021
00:51:50,610 --> 00:51:52,520
[A few days before Amy's shoot]

1022
00:51:52,520 --> 00:51:55,440
- Hello.
- Hello, hello.

1023
00:51:55,440 --> 00:51:57,640
[Avengers directors meet Amy for the first time]

1024
00:51:57,640 --> 00:51:59,540
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

1025
00:51:59,540 --> 00:52:01,960
I'm Amy.

1026
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:05,210
Did you hear what we are adapting?

1027
00:52:05,210 --> 00:52:06,610
- Yes, "Do Ri, Do Shim."
- Did you read it?

1028
00:52:06,610 --> 00:52:07,970
Yes, I finished it.

1029
00:52:07,970 --> 00:52:12,600
Do Shim is supposed to be very tall.

1030
00:52:12,600 --> 00:52:16,390
You're dressed just like her in the poster.

1031
00:52:16,390 --> 00:52:19,280
